6 A BILL
7 TO BE ENTITLED
8 AN ACT
9
10 Relating to the Alabama Sunset Law; to continue the
11 existence and functioning of the Alabama Massage Therapy
12 Licensing Board until October 1, 2027, with certain
13 modifications; to amend Sections 34-43A-2, 34-43A-4, 34-43A-5,
14 34-43A-6, 34-43A-7, 34-43A-8, 34-43A-9, and 34-43A-10, as last
15 amended by Act 2025-395, 2025 Regular Session, Section
16 34-43A-11, Sections 34-43A-12, 34-43A-13, 34-43A-14,
17 34-43A-16, 34-43A-18, as last amended by Act 2025-395, 2025
18 Regular Session, and Section 34-43A-19, Code of Alabama 1975,,
19 to rename the board as the Alabama Massage Therapy Advisory
20 Council; to provide the Alabama Department of Public Health
21 with regulatory authority over massage therapists, massage
22 therapy establishments, and massage therapy schools; to
23 require the council to advise the department on matters
24 relating to massage therapy; to provide for the duties and
25 powers of the department, the State Health Officer, and the
26 State Committee of Public Health; and to transfer all property
27 of the council to the department.
28 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
Page 1

BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
SB136 Engrossed
29 Section 1. Pursuant to the Alabama Sunset Law, the
30 Sunset Committee recommends the continuance of the Alabama
31 Massage Therapy Licensing Board until October 1, 2026, with
32 additional recommendation for statutory change as set out in
33 Section 3.
34 Section 2. The existence and functioning of the Alabama
35 Massage Therapy Licensing Board, created and functioning
36 pursuant to Sections 34-43A-1 to 34-43A-19, inclusive, Code of
37 Alabama 1975, is continued until October 1 2026, and those
38 code sections are expressly preserved.
39 Section 3. Sections 34-43A-2, 34-43A-4, 34-43A-5,
40 34-43A-6, 34-43A-7, 34-43A-8, 34-43A-9, and 34-43A-10, as last
41 amended by Act 2025-395, 2025 Regular Session, Section
42 34-43A-11, Sections 34-43A-12, 34-43A-13, 34-43A-14,
43 34-43A-16, 34-43A-18, as last amended by Act 2025-395, 2025
44 Regular Session, and Section 34-43A-19, Code of Alabama 1975,
45 are amended to read as follows:
