144 "§34-43A-4
145 (a) The following individuals, offices, and
146 establishments are exempt from this chapter:
147 (1) A student who is rendering massage therapy services
148 under the supervision of a massage therapy instructor. A
149 student shall be designated by title clearly indicating his or
150 her training status.
151 (2) An individual practicing massage therapy pursuant
152 to a temporary permit issued by the board department.
153 (3) A qualified member of another profession who is
154 licensed and regulated under state law rendering services that
155 are within the scope of his or her license, provided that the
156 individual does not represent himself or herself as a massage
157 therapist.
158 (4) An individual providing massages to his or her
159 immediate family.
160 (5) An individual offering massage therapy instruction
161 who is visiting from another state, territory, or country,
162 provided that the individual is licensed or registered as
163 required in his or her place of residence. A visiting
164 instructor may teach continuing education courses in this
165 state for up to 100 hours per year without being licensed by
166 the board department. A visiting instructor who teaches
167 continuing education courses in this state for 100 hours or
168 more per year is required to be licensed by the board
Page 6

more per year is required to be licensed by the board
