197 "§34-43A-5
198 (a)(1) There is created the Alabama Massage Therapy
199 Licensing Board. Commencing on October 1, 2026, the board is
200 renamed the Alabama Massage Therapy Advisory Council. The
201 purpose of the board advisory council is to protect advise the
202 department on all matters pertaining to the protection of the
203 health, safety, and welfare of the public by ensuring that
204 relating to massage therapists, massage therapy schools,
205 massage therapy establishments, and massage therapy
206 instructors meet prescribed standards of education,
207 competency, and practice. To accomplish this mission, the
208 board shall establish standards to ensure completion of all
209 board functions in a timely and effective manner and to
210 provide open and immediate access to all relevant public
211 information. The board shall communicate its responsibilities
212 and services to the public as part of its consumer protection
213 duties. The board shall develop and implement a long range
214 plan to ensure effective regulation and consumer protection.
215 All members serving on the Alabama Massage Therapy Licensing
216 Board on October 1, 2026, shall continue to serve as members
217 of the Alabama Massage Therapy Advisory Council until the
218 expiration of their terms.
219 (2) All On October 1, 2026, all rights, duties,
220 records, property, real or personal, and all other effects
221 existing in the name of the Alabama Board of Massage Therapy,
222 formerly created and functioning pursuant to Chapter 43, or in
223 any other name by which that board has been known, shall
224 continue in the name of the Alabama Massage Therapy Licensing
Page 8

continue in the name of the Alabama Massage Therapy Licensing
