427 "§34-43A-7
428 (a) No individual may perform the duties of a massage
429 therapist in this state unless he or she holds a valid license
430 issued by the board department.
431 (b) A massage therapist may not perform massage therapy
432 for a sexually-oriented business, and shall be subject to
433 Article 3 of Chapter 12 of Title 13A.
434 (c) A massage therapist may not advertise or offer to
435 perform services outside the scope of his or her expertise,
436 experience, and education for any client who is ill or has a
437 physical dysfunction, unless the services are performed in
438 conjunction with a licensed physician, physical therapist, or
439 chiropractor.
440 (d) A massage therapist or massage therapy
441 establishment may not advertise or offer to perform services
442 on any sexually explicit website or online platform that
443 promotes prostitution, sexually explicit services, or human
444 trafficking.
445 (e) Unless exempt pursuant to Section 34-43A-4, a
446 massage therapist may only perform massage therapy services at
447 or through a licensed massage therapy establishment. If a
448 massage therapist is performing outcall massage therapy
Page 16

massage therapist is performing outcall massage therapy
SB136 Engrossed
449 services, those services shall be provided through a licensed
450 massage therapy establishment."
451 "§34-43A-8
452 (a) An individual desiring to be licensed as a massage
453 therapist shall apply to the board department on forms
454 provided by the board department. Unless licensed pursuant to
455 subsection (b), an applicant for a license shall submit
456 evidence satisfactory to the board department that he or she
457 has met all of the following requirements:
458 (1) Successfully completed a course of instruction in
459 massage therapy which meets the minimum criteria established
460 by board committee rule for course content and hours of
461 instruction. To perform therapeutic massage on an animal, a
462 massage therapist shall have also graduated from a nationally
463 approved program and completed at least 100 hours of
464 postgraduate training and education in animal anatomy,
465 pathology, and physiology for the specific type of animal upon
466 which he or she will perform therapeutic massage.
467 (2) Successfully passed a state board exam or a
468 national standardized examination approved by the board
469 committee. The board committee may approve other state exams
470 on a case-by-case basis.
471 (3) Completed a criminal history background check
472 pursuant to Section 34-43A-13(c). The board department may
473 deny or discipline an applicant who has been convicted of a
474 felony or of any crime arising out of or connected with the
475 practice of massage therapy.
476 (4) Paid all applicable fees.
Page 17

(4) Paid all applicable fees.
SB136 Engrossed
477 (5) Additional requirements as provided by rule.
478 (b) Notwithstanding the requirements listed in
479 subdivisions (a)(1) and (a)(2), the board department may
480 license an applicant who is licensed or registered to practice
481 massage therapy in another state if the standards of practice
482 or licensing of that state, at the time the applicant was
483 originally licensed or registered, were equal to or stricter
484 than the requirements imposed by this chapter. All applicants
485 may be subject to an initial in-person board hearing at the
486 discretion of the board.
487 (c) Upon receipt of an application, the board
488 department shall notify the applicant that his or her
489 application is complete and shall also notify the applicant
490 upon the approval of his or her application. An application is
491 not complete until all components of the application have been
492 received and all criminal history information has been
493 delivered to the board department. If an application is
494 proposed to be rejected, the applicant shall be entitled to a
495 hearing on his or her application."
