613 "§34-43A-13
614 (a) Any individual may file with the board department a
615 written complaint regarding an allegation of impropriety by a
616 massage therapist, massage therapy establishment, or other
Page 22

massage therapist, massage therapy establishment, or other
SB136 Engrossed
617 individual or entity. Complaints shall be made in the manner
618 prescribed by the board department.
619 (b) The executive director department shall provide for
620 an investigation of the complaint and, if probable cause is
621 found, may initiate an administrative proceeding. Upon a
622 finding that the licensee or applicant for licensing has
623 committed any of the following misconduct, the board
624 department may suspend, revoke, probate, reprimand, otherwise
625 discipline, or refuse to issue or renew a license or impose a
626 civil penalty after notice and opportunity for a hearing
627 pursuant to the Administrative Procedure Act:
628 (1) Obtained or attempted to obtain a license by means
629 of fraud, misrepresentation, fraudulent transcripts,
630 invalidated exam scores, or concealment of material facts,
631 including making a false statement on an application or any
632 other document required by the board department for licensing.
633 (2) Sold or bartered, or offered to sell or barter, a
634 license for a massage therapist or a massage therapy
635 establishment.
636 (3) Has engaged in unprofessional conduct that has
637 endangered or is likely to endanger the health, safety, and
638 welfare of the public, as defined by the rules of the board
639 committee.
640 (4) Has been convicted of a felony or of any crime
641 arising out of or connected with the practice of massage
642 therapy.
643 (5) Has violated or aided and abetted in the violation
644 of this chapter.
Page 23

of this chapter.
SB136 Engrossed
645 (6) Is adjudicated as mentally incompetent by a court
646 of law.
647 (7) Uses controlled substances or habitually and
648 excessively uses alcohol.
649 (8) Engaged in false, deceptive, or misleading
650 advertising.
651 (9) Engaged in or attempted to or offered to engage a
652 client in sexual activity, including, but not limited to,
653 genital contact, within the client-massage therapist
654 relationship.
655 (10) Has knowingly allowed the massage therapy
656 establishment to be used as an overnight sleeping
657 accommodation.
658 (11) Had a license revoked, suspended, or denied in any
