874 "§34-43A-19
875 (a) The board is subject to the Alabama Sunset Law of
876 1981, and is classified as an enumerated agency pursuant to
877 Section 41-20-3. The board shall automatically terminate on
878 October 1, 2026, and every four years thereafter, unless
879 continued pursuant to the Alabama Sunset Law.
880 (b) The board department shall adopt a program of
881 continuing education for licensees which shall be a requisite
882 for the renewal of licenses issued pursuant to this chapter
883 and not exceed the requirements of a board-approved nationally
884 recognized board certification organization such as the
885 National Certification Board for Therapeutic Massage and
886 Bodywork.
887 Section 4. The Legislature concurs in the
888 recommendations of the Sunset Committee as provided in
889 Sections 1, 2, and 3.
890 Section 5. This act shall become effective October 1,
891 2026.
